Human: Determine the nonnegative integers that have an even sum of digits.
The sum of digits of an integer is 2 greater than the sum of digits of its factors. The integers satisfying this condition are those that do not have an odd digit sum. Write a Python program to print all such integers.

Assistant: """
Program to determine nonnegative integers that have an even sum of digits
"""
def isEvenNum(n): 
    if(n==1): 
        return True
    assert n >= 1
    if(n % 10 == 0):
        return 0
    if(n % 2 == 0):
        return 0
    m = n//10
    return 1 if m % 2 == 0 else 0
def evenNums(n): 
    num = 1
    for i in range(n+1): 
        if isEvenNum(i): 
            print(num,end=" ")
            num += 1
    print()
n = int(input())
even_N = 0
for i in range(n+1):
    if(i%2==0 and isEvenNum(i)):
        even_N += 1
print("The nonnegative integers that have an even sum of digits are:")
for i in range(even_N):
    print(i,end=" ")
